   "source": [
    "**1.4** The census data only contains records that apply for the period 2008-2012, while the crime dataset runs from 2001-2024. \n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, begin by filtering the crime data so that you get a dataframe that contains records only for the period 2008-2012. \n",
    "\n",
    "*Hint*: You'll be filtering based on date quite alot in this project, and it's therefore very advisable to transform the existing *Date* column into datetime-format. \n",
    "\n",
    "To simplify further, you could perhaps also create new columns that indicate *Year*, *Month*, *Day* and *Hour*. \n",
    "\n",
    "You might also find that other types of indicator columns could be useful. Feel free to come back and add them here later.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Important:** For the remainder of this project, we will only work with data for the year 2008-2012."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Convert the 'Date' column to datetime format\n",
    "\n",
    "chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Date'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create indicator columns for Year, Month, Day and Hour\n",
    "chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Year'] = chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Date'].dt.year\n",
    "chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Month'] = chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Date'].dt.month\n",
    "chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Day'] = chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Date'].dt.day\n",
    "chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Hour'] = chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Date'].dt.hour\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add month and day name\n",
    "chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Month_Name'] = chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Date'].dt.month_name()\n",
    "chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Weekday'] = chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Date'].dt.day_name()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# create a new dataframe with crime records only the period 2008-2012\n",
    "\n",
    "year_2008_to_2012_filter = (\n",
    "    (chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Year'] >= 2008) &\n",
    "    (chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df['Year'] <= 2012)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "chicago_crime_2008_to_2012_df = chicago_crime_2001_to_2025_df[year_2008_to_2012_filter].reset_index(drop=True)"
   ]
  },
