    "To better understand whether prostitution incidents concentrate in specific areas of Chicago, I generated a spatial density map using the available latitude and longitude values.\n",
    "\n",
    "The plot divides Chicago into a grid of hexagonal cells and colors each cell according to the number of cases occurring there. Darker colors indicate a higher concentration of incidents.\n",
    "\n",
    "The visualization clearly shows a strong hotspot in the West Side of Chicago, around the area near latitude 41.88° and longitude –87.75°.\n",
    "This cluster stands out significantly compared to the rest of the city, suggesting that prostitution activity on Friday nights is not evenly distributed, but instead concentrated in a specific region.\n",
    "\n",
