   "source": [
    "To explore whether other crime categories show geographical concentration—similar to prostitution on Friday nights. I generated interactive map visualizations for different crime types, weekdays, and day/night periods. Using the same function I built for question 9.2, I plotted several combinations to compare spatial patterns across Chicago.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Motor Vehicle Theft – Friday Nights**\n",
    "\n",
    "The map shows that vehicle theft on Friday nights is highly concentrated in the North Side and central areas near Lake Michigan, with additional clusters spreading westward into residential zones. This indicates that nighttime mobility and parking density likely play a role in these hotspots.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Battery – Saturday Nights**\n",
    "\n",
    "Battery incidents on Saturday nights show a similar but slightly more widespread pattern, covering both the central districts and the western neighborhoods. The concentration appears more dispersed compared to vehicle theft, suggesting different underlying behavioral patterns or social activity during weekend nights."
   ]
